<subSubSection id="F6B276F9FFF4B609B7F2FF31FDC5FCE2" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="description">
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7F2FF31FEF0FF0E" blockId="14.[151,915,151,213]" box="[151,274,187,213]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B7FAFF31FF0CFF0E" box="[159,238,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[168,1419,181,1859]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—♂HT, northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province, Dong Van district; C–D—PT ♀—ditto HT; E–F—R. latifasciata Leech, ♂Type; B.M. Type NoRh 2682, China, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141965; G–H—R. latifasciata Leech, ♀Cotype; B.M. Type NoRh 2683, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141963" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556620/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B79EFF31FEE8FF0E" box="[251,266,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[345,1243,190,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[345,1243,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male genitalia of A—Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. (northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province); B—R. l. crystallina Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. (central Vietnam, Thua Thien Hue province); C—R. l. critias Riley &amp; Godfrey, (southern China, southern Yunnan)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7F2FE89FD1BFEC5" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,1401]" box="[151,761,259,286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B7F2FE89FEC9FEC6" bold="true" box="[151,299,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Description:</emphasis>
Male. Length of forewing: HT 22.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7A2FEA2FEC7FDC2" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
<specimenCount id="A8AEEEFBFFF4B609B7A2FEA2FF3EFE99" box="[199,220,296,322]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B787FEADFEBFFE9A" bold="true" box="[226,349,295,321]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Upperside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B60FFEADFE02FE9A" box="[362,480,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[168,1419,181,1859]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—♂HT, northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province, Dong Van district; C–D—PT ♀—ditto HT; E–F—R. latifasciata Leech, ♂Type; B.M. Type NoRh 2682, China, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141965; G–H—R. latifasciata Leech, ♀Cotype; B.M. Type NoRh 2683, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141963" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556620/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figure 8A</figureCitation>
). Ground colour of both wings blackish with a broad, white postdiscal band broadened at dorsum on the forewing and to the costal edge on the hindwing; on the forewing the band ends at vein M 
<subScript id="222C2737FFF4B609B2E8FED4FA77FEB7" attach="left" box="[1421,1429,350,364]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">1</subScript>
. Basal and sub-basal whitish fasciae on the forewing are indistinct. 
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B4C7FEE5FBFFFE52" bold="true" box="[930,1053,367,393]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Underside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B34AFEE5FB45FE52" box="[1071,1191,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[168,1419,181,1859]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—♂HT, northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province, Dong Van district; C–D—PT ♀—ditto HT; E–F—R. latifasciata Leech, ♂Type; B.M. Type NoRh 2682, China, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141965; G–H—R. latifasciata Leech, ♀Cotype; B.M. Type NoRh 2683, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141963" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556620/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figure 8B</figureCitation>
). Both wings ground colour blackish with broad postdiscal white band and well distinct basal, sub-basal and submarginal whitish fasciae. Forewing with series of submarginal eye spots including spots in cells from Cu 
<subScript id="222C2737FFF4B609B37DFE43FBCBFE0C" attach="left" box="[1048,1065,457,471]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">1b</subScript>
(double spot) to R 
<subScript id="222C2737FFF4B609B39BFE40FAE4FE03" attach="left" box="[1278,1286,458,472]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">4</subScript>
(single spots in all other cells); hindwing with series of subterminal eye ringed spots spreading from cell Cu 
<subScript id="222C2737FFF4B609B3DAFE67FB32FE20" attach="left" box="[1215,1232,493,507]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">1b</subScript>
to Rs; spot in cell M 
<subScript id="222C2737FFF4B609B7D5FD98FF5AFDFB" attach="left" box="[176,184,530,544]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">1</subScript>
is absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7A2FDA9FCECFDE5" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,1401]" box="[199,782,547,574]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
Female: length of forewing: PTs 24.0; 24.5; 
<quantity id="79508897FFF4B609B5DDFDA9FCE8FDE5" box="[696,778,547,574]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7A2FDC2FE18FD72" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
<specimenCount id="A8AEEEFBFFF4B609B7A2FDC2FF3EFDB9" box="[199,220,584,610]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B78FFDCDFE9CFDB9" box="[234,382,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[168,1419,181,1859]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—♂HT, northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province, Dong Van district; C–D—PT ♀—ditto HT; E–F—R. latifasciata Leech, ♂Type; B.M. Type NoRh 2682, China, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141965; G–H—R. latifasciata Leech, ♀Cotype; B.M. Type NoRh 2683, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141963" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556620/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figure 8C, D</figureCitation>
) The female is slightly larger than the male with a convex terminal edge on the forewing; wing patterns on both surfaces are similar to that in the male. The most conspicuous character is the absence of an eye spot in cell M 
<subScript id="222C2737FFF4B609B657FD28FED8FD6B" attach="left" box="[306,314,674,688]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">1</subScript>
of the hindwing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7A2FD39FDC5FCE2" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B7A2FD39FE98FD16" bold="true" box="[199,378,691,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B6EFFD39FE0CFD16" box="[394,494,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[345,1243,190,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[345,1243,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male genitalia of A—Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. (northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province); B—R. l. crystallina Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. (central Vietnam, Thua Thien Hue province); C—R. l. critias Riley &amp; Godfrey, (southern China, southern Yunnan)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figure 9</figureCitation>
). Uncus long, slender and gradually tapering at tip; uncus in 1.5 times longer than tegumen and pointed towards the tip; gnathos is ½ of the uncus length and pointed towards the end; saccus relatively long but shorter than valvae; phallus long with hooked bend at the tip; valvae elongated with the round apex and small and small spike at upper side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B276F9FFF4B609B7A2FCC9FD03FB1E" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF4B609B7A2FCC9FD03FB1E" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,1401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B7A2FCC9FEA0FC86" bold="true" box="[199,322,835,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Specimens recently collected in 
<collectingRegion id="7C6CEB90FFF4B609B5D2FCCEFCC1FC86" box="[695,803,835,862]" inferredBySuffix="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Ha Giang</collectingRegion>
province are similar to the 
<specimenCount id="A8AEEEFBFFF4B609B339FCCEFB93FC85" box="[1116,1137,836,862]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="A8AEEEFBFFF4B609B3CCFCCEFB5CFC85" box="[1193,1214,836,862]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B3A3FCCEFA86FC86" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[1222,1380,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B3A3FCCEFA86FC86" box="[1222,1380,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">R. latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF4B609B209FCCEFA7EFC85" box="[1388,1436,836,862]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">type</typeStatus>
specimens described from Moupin [Baoxing, 
<collectingRegion id="7C6CEB90FFF4B609B5F2FCECFD16FC5A" box="[663,756,870,897]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
] (W. 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B454FCEDFC94FC59" box="[817,886,871,898]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">China</collectingCountry>
) and deposited in the NHM. It is definitely a rare species that has not been collected or mentioned since Leech’s (1892–94) publication of the species description. Recently, the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B6E7FC25FDE2FC12" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[386,512,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B6E7FC25FDE2FC12" box="[386,512,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was misidentified as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B4A7FC3AFBDEFC12" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1862" box="[962,1084,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crisilda">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B4A7FC3AFBDEFC12" box="[962,1084,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">R. crisilda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="DA395883FFF4B609B30DFC3AFB1AFC12" author="Lang, S. Y." box="[1128,1272,943,970]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" refId="ref12607" refString="Lang, S. Y. (2017) The Nymphalidae of China (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). Part II: Satyrinae (partim), Tribe Satyrini (partim), Subtribes Eritina, Ragadiina, Lethina, Parargina. Tshikolovets Publications, Pardubice-Beibei, 200 pp., 73 pls." type="book" year="2017">Lang (2017)</bibRefCitation>
and has been regarded as a form of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B6EDFC5EFE1EFC36" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1862" box="[392,508,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crisilda">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B6EDFC5EFE1EFC36" box="[392,508,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">R. crisilda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF4B609B51EFC5EFD49FC35" box="[635,683,980,1006]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B42CFC59FC25FC36" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[841,967,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B42CFC59FC25FC36" box="[841,967,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B36CFC59FBAEFC36" box="[1033,1100,979,1005]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">China</collectingCountry>
and the recent discovery from 
<collectingRegion id="7C6CEB90FFF4B609B7F2FC72FEE7FBCA" box="[151,261,1015,1042]" country="Vietnam" name="Ha Giang" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Ha Giang</collectingRegion>
bear no resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B57AFC72FD74FBCA" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1862" box="[543,662,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crisilda">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B57AFC72FD74FBCA" box="[543,662,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">R. crisilda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has a complete series of submarginal spots on the hindwing underside. The wing patterns of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B565FB96FD7FFBEE" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[512,669,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B565FB96FD7FFBEE" box="[512,669,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">R. latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B4FBFB96FAEEFBEE" authority="Riley &amp; Godfrey, 1921" authorityName="Riley &amp; Godfrey" authorityYear="1921" box="[926,1292,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="critias">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B4FBFB96FBE6FBEE" box="[926,1028,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">R. critias</emphasis>
Riley &amp; Godfrey, 1921
</taxonomicName>
from central 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B7F2FBB5FF1BFB82" box="[151,249,1087,1113]" name="Vietnam" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, which can be easily distinguished from specimens from the 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF4B609B4F8FBCAFC2FFB81" box="[925,973,1088,1114]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">type</typeStatus>
locality (N. 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B33DFBB5FB5FFB81" box="[1112,1213,1087,1114]" name="Thailand" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Thailand</collectingCountry>
) and from Southern 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B7F2FBE9FF38FBA6" box="[151,218,1123,1149]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="7C6CEB90FFF4B609B78CFBE9FE4FFBA6" box="[233,429,1123,1149]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
, near the border to 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B5ECFBE9FD0FFBA5" box="[649,749,1123,1150]" name="Vietnam" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
). At the same time, the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B3D8FBE9FAD9FBA6" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[1213,1339,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B3D8FBE9FAD9FBA6" box="[1213,1339,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from N. 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B7F2FB0DFF14FB7A" box="[151,246,1159,1185]" name="Vietnam" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF4B609B648FB02FE97FB7A" authorityName="Riley &amp; Godfrey" authorityYear="1921" box="[301,373,1160,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="critias">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF4B609B648FB02FE97FB7A" box="[301,373,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">critias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from C. 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B6BEFB0DFDDFFB7A" box="[475,573,1159,1185]" name="Vietnam" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B52DFB0DFD4EFB7A" box="[584,684,1159,1185]" name="Thailand" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and S. 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF4B609B464FB0DFCA6FB7A" box="[769,836,1159,1185]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">China</collectingCountry>
show high similarity (
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF4B609B324FB0DFB5FFB7A" box="[1089,1213,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,561,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-198@15.[154,1434,561,1867]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. A–B—Ragadia latifasciata critias Riley &amp; Godfrey, 1921 stat. rev., ♂—southern China; C–D—R. latifasciata crystallina Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov., ♂HT—central Vietnam, Thua Thien Hue province, Bach Ma N.P.; E–F—Ditto, ♀PT—central Vietnam, Kon Tum province." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556626/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figures 10</figureCitation>
). Considering these observations, we suggest a revision of these species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
